text.section:
The Kentucky Public Service Commission shall produce consumer education materials that:
Describe Kentucky's telemarketing laws;
Describe the consumer's rights and responsibilities regarding the receipt of telephone solicitation;
Explain how consumers can apply to be placed on any federal Do Not Call Registry established by the Federal Communications Commission and the Federal Trade Commission;
Explain how to apply to be placed on company-specific and industrywide no solicitation calls list, including those lists provided by the Direct Marketing Association (DMA) and the Telephone Preference Service (TPS); and
Describe how a consumer can file a complaint if the consumer receives calls after being placed on the Do Not Call Registry established by the Federal Communications Commission and the Federal Trade Commission.
